<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-8463] Fix redundant reassignment of tasks when leader worker leaves</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8463</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s a bug in the computation of new assignment for connectors and tasks in &lt;tt&gt;IncrementalCooperativeAssignor&lt;/tt&gt; that may lead to duplicate assignment. The existing assignments should always be considered because if the leader worker bounces there&apos;s no history of previous assignments.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
